Organic acidemias are a group of metabolic disorders characterized by the accumulation of abnormal amounts and types of organic acids in the body. However, the presence of specific symptoms like dicarboxylic aciduria, 3-methylglutaric aciduria, and elevated urinary carboxylic acid suggest a more specific type of organic acidemia, such as propionic acidemia or methylmalonic acidemia. Metabolic acidosis is not a primary symptom of urea cycle disorders, but it can occur as a secondary complication.
